IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: TO PRESERVE AND PROTECT SCENIC, HISTORIC AND RECREATIONAL LANDS WITH HIGH NATURAL RESOURCE VALUES.
IRS990.MissionDesc: TO PRESERVE AND PROTECT SCENIC, HISTORIC AND RECREATIONAL LANDS WITH HIGH NATURAL RESOURCE VALUES IN THE GREATER TRUCKEE DONNER REGION AND MANAGE RECREATIONAL ACTIVITIES ON THESE LANDS IN A SUSTAINABLE MANNER.
IRS990.Desc: STEWARDSHIP:STEWARDSHIP CONTINUES TO COMPLETE A LOT OF PROJECTS. FROG LAKE BACK COUNTRY HUTS HAD ITS FIRST FULL YEAR OF OPERATIONS WITH OVER 90% OCCUPANCY IN BOTH WINTER AND SUMMER MONTHS. IT'S HAD IT'S CHALLENGES WITH GENERATOR/SOLAR PROBLEMS AND SNOW REMOVAL. WE COMPLETED MANY FORESTRY AND FUEL REDUCTION PROJECTS AND HAVE GRANTS FOR A LOT MORE IN THE SUBSEQUENT YEAR. TRAIL MAINTENANCE IS ALWAYS AN ONGOING DUTY AND WE HAVE COMPLETED NEW TRAILS ON THE WADDELL RANCH PROPERTY. CONSTRUCTION HAS BEGUN ON THE TRUCKEE SPRINGS BRIDGE AND TRAILHEAD IN PARTNERSHIP WITH THE TOWN OF TRUCKEE.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: LANDS:LAND ACQUISITIONS IN THE YEAR WERE NOT SIGNIFICANT AS IT TAKES SOMETIMES MANY YEARS FOR A DEAL TO BE COMPLETE. WE CURRENTLY HAVE 3 VERY LARGE LAND ACQUISITIONS IN THE WORKS, 2 WHICH ARE UNDER CONTRACT AND 1 THAT IS STILL BEING NEGOTIATED. A GRANT OF $200K WAS RECEIVED IN ADVANCE FOR ONE OF THESE ACQUISITIONS. WE ARE ALSO NEGOTIATING WITH THE US FOREST SERVICE TO TRANSFER TWO TDLT OWNED PARCELS OVER TO THEM WHICH WE HOPE TO COMPLETE BY THE END OF THE CURRENT FISCAL YEAR.

Form990ScheduleAPartVIGrp.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: SCHEDULE A, PART II, LINE 10, EXPLANATION OF OTHER INCOME:

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION SUPPORTED THE COMMITTEE FOR A RESILIENT TRUCKEE IN SUPPORT OF THE "YES" ON MEASURE T FIRE PREVENTION.

THE LAND TRUST POLICY IS TO CULTIVATE A PROACTIVE AND POSITIVE RELATIONSHIP WITH LANDOWNERS TO AVOID EASEMENT VIOLATIONS. THIS IS DONE THROUGH INITIAL EDUCATION AND ANNUAL MONITORING AND REGULAR COMMUNICATION. DOCUMENTATION OF BASELINES, ANNUAL MONITORING, VIOLATIONS, COMMUNICATIONS, AND CORRECTIVE ACTIONS ARE ALL ESSENTIAL AND REQUIRED IN THE POLICY. IN THE EVENT OF A VIOLATION, COOPERATIVE RESOLUTION AND CORRECTION WITH THE LANDOWNER IS SOUGHT. IF THIS IS NOT POSSIBLE, MEDIATION AND/OR LITIGTAION IS UTILIZED TO THE EXTENT NECESSARY.

CONSERVATION EASEMENTS ARE VALUED AT APPRAISED VALUE OR COST AT TIME OF ACQUISITION, DEPENDING UPON WHETHER THE EASEMENT IS PURCHASED OR DONATED. WHEN DONATED, DONATION REVENUE IS EQUAL TO THE VALUE OF THE EASEMENT IS RECOGNIZED. CONSERVATION EASEMENTS ARE EXPENSED AS LANDS DONATED TO THE PUBLIC IN THE YEAR ACQUIRED AND ARE NOT CAPITALIZED ON THE BALANCE SHEET.

THE ENDOWMENT CONSISTS OF FOUR INDIVIDUAL FUNDS ESTABLISHED BY DONORS TO PROVIDE ANNUAL FUNDING FOR SPECIFIC ACTIVITIES AND GENERAL OPERATIONS. THE ENDOWMENT ALSO INCLUDES CERTAIN NET ASSETS WITHOUT DONOR RESTRICTIONS DESIGNATED FOR LONG-TERM FUNDS BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS THAT ARE MANAGED SIMILAR TO ENDOWMENTS. NET ASSETS ASSOCIATED WITH ENDOWMENT FUNDS ARE CLASSIFIED AND REPORTED BASED ON THE EXISTENCE OR ABSENCE OF DONOR-IMPOSED RESTRICTIONS.
THE LAND TRUST HAD APPLIED THE ACCOUNTING PRINCIPLES RELATED TO ACCOUNTING FOR UNCERTAINTY IN INCOME TAXES AND HAS DETERMINED THAT THERE IS NO MATERIAL IMPACT ON THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS.

RecipientBusinessName.BusinessNameLine1Txt: COMMITTEE FOR TRAILS-YES ON MEASURE U

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: GOVERNMENT GRANTS ARE AWARDED TO GOVERNMENTAL AGENCIES TO SUPPORT SPECIFIC PROGRAMS. NO MONITORING REPORTS ARE REQUIRED AND THE GOVERNMENT RESULTS ARE KNOWN BY THE TRUCKEE DONNER LAND TRUST. OTHER GRANTS WERE PAID TO LOBBYING ORGANIZATIONS TO SUPPORT THE PASSAGE OF FIRE PREVENTION MEASURE T. MONITORING OF SUCH GRANTS IS NOT REQUIRED.
THE NUMBER OF DONORS IS DETERMINED BY SPECIFIC IDENTIFICATION.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 8B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: COMMITTEE REPORTS ARE SUBMITTED AND REVIEWED AT THE QUARTERLY BOD MEETINGS BUT WRITTEN DOCUMENTATION IS NOT REQUIRED.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE 990 IS REVIEWED BY THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR AND FINANCE COMMITTEE. AFTER THIS REVIEW AND COMMENTS, THE FINAL VERSION IS DISTRIBUTED TO THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS FOR REVIEW AND APPROVAL BEFORE FILING WITH THE IRS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: EACH YEAR THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS ARE REQUIRED TO REVIEW THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY AND DISCLOSE ANY CONFLICTS. FOR EACH LAND DEAL, THE BOARD PRESIDENT AND EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR CONSIDER POTENTIAL CONFLICTS OF INTEREST FOR THEMSELVES OR ANY OTHER BOARD MEMBER. ADDITIONALLY, IT IS ENCUMBENT UPON EACH BOARD MEMBER TO PONDER AND DIVULGE ANY CONFLICT OF INTEREST FOR EACH DEAL.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: A PERFORMANCE REVIEW OF THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR IS DONE ANNUALLY WITH A CORRESPONDING REVIEW AND APPROVAL OF ANNUAL COMPENSATION BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS AS PART OF THE BUDGET APPROVAL PROCESS. IN ORDER TO EVALUATE THE REASONABILITY OF COMPENSATION FOR ALL EMPLOYEES, OTHER REGIONAL LAND TRUSTS, AS WELL AS OTHER REGIONAL NONPROFITS OF SIMILAR SIZE ARE QUERIED. ALSO COMPENSATION DATA PUBLISHED BY THE LAND TRUST ALLIANCE MAY BE CONSIDERED. THIS PROCESS WAS LAST UNDERTAKEN IN 2023. BOARD MEMBERS/OFFICERS OF THE CORPORATION ARE VOLUNTEERS AND ARE NOT COMPENSATED.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, FINANCIAL INFORMATION, AND POLICIES ARE AVAILABLE UPON REQUEST TO THE ORGANIZATION'S ADMINISTRATIVE OFFICE. ADDITIONALLY, MANY DOCUMENTS ARE AVAILABLE UPON REQUEST IN PDF VIA EMAIL. ANNUAL TAX RETURN AND AUDIT IS POSTED ON TDLT WEBSITE.
